<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>EQs PvP problems have naught to do with your post</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?TheBlack[BCK]">TheBlack[BCK]</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 4:30 p.m. 16/2/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> EQs PvP problems have naught to do with your post<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/pvp.cgi?read=893" TARGET=_self>Why there aren't alot of people in pvp server!</A> (Druez the Quick)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>

<BR>Granted the problem with finding others to PvP against is an issue, one that should be solved by the PvP server. Moving on...
<P>&gt; Here are some suggestions, First of lots of pvp players fight
<BR>&gt; for loot, you have to allow full looting. Second, there should
<BR>&gt; be no level method at all as far as attacking goes. Make the
<BR>&gt; towns safe where you can fight but guards will attack the
<BR>&gt; agressor also. Not super uo guards just like the guards you
<BR>&gt; have. Allow bounty method of placing gold on peoples head. Also
<BR>&gt; you have to keep in exp loss. Hmm that about raps it up.
<P>Full looting is a terrible idea for EQ. Removing level limits is an equally bad idea for a level oriented game.
<P>EQ has a lot of problems with PvP and fixing some of them will go a long way towards improving the game, but neither of your suggestions will help the PvP community.
<P>&gt; Remember one thing on Catskills alone there are litterly 2000
<BR>&gt; people who pvp daily. If you don't belive me look at there guild
<BR>&gt; lists for order chaos guilds and the amount of wars going on.
<P>&gt; You have to support pvp in a big or you are limiting your
<BR>&gt; marketabiltiy.
<P>&gt; Thanks
<P>Definitely there are lots of PvP players out there, I estimate tens of thousands. Supporting PvP makes good $$$ sense to Verant. But lets focus on improving the PVP sytem of the game, not introducing ways to limit or destroy it.
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
